prmana: OIDC Authentication for Unix/Linux Systems

A PAM module and client agent enabling OpenID Connect (OIDC) authentication
for SSH and sudo on Unix/Linux systems, with DPoP (Demonstrating Proof of
Possession) support for enhanced token security.

Project Homepage: https://github.com/prodnull/prmana

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This project implements the following IETF standards:
- RFC 6749: OAuth 2.0 Authorization Framework
- RFC 8628: OAuth 2.0 Device Authorization Grant
- RFC 9449: OAuth 2.0 Demonstrating Proof of Possession (DPoP)
- RFC 7638: JSON Web Key (JWK) Thumbprint
- RFC 7519: JSON Web Token (JWT)
- RFC 8693: OAuth 2.0 Token Exchange

